
Overview of verb beckon

The verb beckon has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (9) beckon, wave -- (signal with the hands or nod; "She waved to her friends"; "He waved his hand hospitably")
2. (1) beckon -- (appear inviting; "The shop window decorations beckoned")
3. beckon -- (summon with a wave, nod, or some other gesture)
